RAM:

RAM, which stands for Random Access Memory, 
is a hardware device generally located on the motherboard of a computer 
and acts as an internal memory of the CPU. It allows CPU store data, program,
and program results when you switch on the computer. It is the read and write memory of a computer,
which means the information can be written to it as well as read from it.
RAM is a volatile memory,
which means it does not store data or instructions permanently.
